\ Problem 2
\ Next define BOX which prints out a rectangle of stars, given the width
\ and height (number of lines), using the stack order ( width height --)

s" stars.fs" included

: +box ( width height --)
	0 do
		dup stars cr \ 'stars' consumes 'width' each time
	loop drop ;

: box ( width height --)
	?dup 0= if exit then \ avoid absurdly long loops
	over 0= if 2drop drop exit then \ +box shouldn't print empty rows

	+box ;

10 3 box
5 5 box
0 8 box
8 0 box
.s
